overview: Nathanial Trienens is Director of Mobile Services and Co-Founder of Fuzz Productions, a Web, Mobile and Social Agency with offices in New York City and Northampton, Massachusetts. He has worked with a wide array of clients to develop and implement their digital strategy, including Kaplan, Rodale, Computer Associates, Ford Models, Sotheby’s and the Author’s Guild. Trienens graduated with Honors from Northwestern University in 1998. Prior to starting Fuzz Productions, he worked for Big Flower Holdings and XL Ventures as a Financial Analyst. He currently teaches a class on iPhone development for the Learning Annex in New York City.
